originalText.text: Zip Care offers one of the worst services in Harlem.  I went there w/a broken toe, sent me to have an xray, took 4 days for the results to get back to me.  Again, Monday, Aug 21 a family member aged 78 was sent for a chest xray, told today it will take up to 5 days for them to get a reading.  They suspect possible pneumonia.  I assume this means...just die.  Nice bedside manner.  Stay away!

originalText.text: I visited ZipCare not too long ago with my niece and I have nothing but positive things to say about my experience. I was greeted by a very sweet girl at the front desk named Michaela who was able to get my insurance and niece's information in a quick and efficient way! My niece was seen by Dr. Gathers who was great at listening and seemed to consider all factors we mentioned when coming to a final assessment for her. Overall, I would say my niece was in safe hands and recommend others to pay this urgent care a visit in their time of need!!

You cant even call to get the physician name or NPI BUMBER or file a complaint. Something is going on over there. it’s always empty yet you have to wait for hours for any responses.

originalText.text:
I was greeted with a friendly "good morning" by Kimberly. She was helping another patient upon my arrival and advised me that she would be with me momentarily. Kim walked me through all of the forms in a clear, concise manner and was eager to help answer any of my questions. She was genuine sweet while remaining professional.
Dr. Gathers did not disappoint. His office is orderly and clean.
I felt like he listened to my concerns, answered my questions, and helped me a great deal address my medical necessity. I had a positive experience there and I'd definitely go there again for urgent care.
